The paper deals with the extension of entropy to mixed-pair random variables, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the application of the extended entropy to complex processes such as queuing networks and caching algorithms, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of entropy preservation to establish non-trivial properties of stochastic processes, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
